The '''State Supplement Program''' (SSP or SSI/SSP), not to be confused with [[Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program|SNAP]], is the state supplement to the U.S. federal [[Supplemental Security Income]] (SSI) program and provides state funded supplement benefits to SSI recipients.<ref>{{USC|7|2015}}(g)</ref>

